articles.title: Deported immigrants, mostly Asian and Latino, will be in Djibouti for 2 weeks, White House says - NBC News
articles.description: A flight with eight immigrants that left Texas this week, reportedly headed for South Sudan, will now remain in the East African country of Djibouti for two weeks to comply with a court order, White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt said on Thursday.
